      "message": "It\u0027s a compilation error:\n\n```\n18:35:58  [ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-compiler-plugin:3.14.1:compile (default-compile) on project org.eclipse.jgit.http.apache: Compilation failure\n18:35:58  [ERROR] /home/jenkins/agent/workspace/stable/jgit-stable.gerrit/repo/org.eclipse.jgit.http.apache/src/org/eclipse/jgit/transport/http/apache/HttpClientConnection.java:[79,14] The type org.eclipse.jgit.transport.http.apache.HttpClientConnection must implement the inherited abstract method org.eclipse.jgit.transport.http.HttpConnection.getErrorStream()\n```\n\nRun `mvn clean verify` locally before pushing.\n\nClass `org.eclipse.jgit.transport.http.apache.HttpClientConnection` in bundle `org.eclipse.jgit.http.apache` needs an implementation of `getErrorStream()`; probably something like\n```\n@Override\npublic InputStream getErrorStream() {\n  if (resp \u003d\u003d null) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  if (resp.getStatusLine().getStatusCode() \u003c HttpStatus.SC_BAD_REQUEST) {\n    // Not an error, so even if there is a message body, it\u0027s not an \"error\" entity.\n    return null;\n  }\n  HttpEntity entity \u003d resp.getEntity();\n  return entity !\u003d null ? entity.getInputStream() : null;\n}\n```\n(This is off the top of my head and completely untested.) Note that you may need to change the interface to specify that `getErrorStream()` may throw an `IOException`.\n\nSuch an implementation for the Apache HTTP client will need to be tested, too.",
